class="blog-markdown mx-auto max-w-screen-md prose prose-hr:h-[8px] prose-hr:m-0 prose-hr:border-none prose-headings:my-0 prose-headings:font-700 prose-headings:text-charcoal prose-h1:mb-[32px] prose-h1:mt-[48px] prose-h1:text-[34px] prose-h1:leading-[40px] prose-h1:tracking-[0.25px] md:prose-h1:text-[48px] md:prose-h1:leading-[56px] md:prose-h1:tracking-[0px] lg:prose-h1:text-[60px] lg:prose-h1:leading-[72px] prose-h2:text-[24px] prose-h2:leading-[32px] prose-h2:tracking-[0px] prose-h2:mt-[48px] prose-h2:mb-[24px] md:prose-h2:text-[34px] md:prose-h2:leading-[40px] md:prose-h2:tracking-[0.25px] lg:prose-h2:text-[40px] lg:prose-h2:leading-[48px] lg:prose-h2:tracking-[0px] prose-h3:text-[20px] prose-h3:leading-[32px] prose-h3:tracking-[0.15px] prose-h3:mb-[20px] md:prose-h3:text-[24px] md:prose-h3:leading-[32px] md:prose-h3:tracking-[0px] prose-p:m-0 prose-p:font-500 prose-p:text-charcoal prose-p:text-[14px] prose-p:leading-[24px] prose-p:tracking-[0.1px] prose-p:mb-[20px] md:prose-p:text-[16px] md:prose-p:leading-[32px] md:prose-p:tracking-[0.15px] prose-a:text-blue prose-strong:font-700 prose-blockquote:border-none prose-blockquote:relative prose-p:before:content-[] prose-blockquote:not-italic prose-blockquote:m-0 prose-blockquote:p-[8px_0px_8px_16px] md:prose-blockquote:p-[8px_0px_8px_26px] prose-blockquote:before:absolute prose-blockquote:before:inset-0 prose-blockquote:before:w-[4px] prose-blockquote:before:bg-blue prose-blockquote:before:rounded-full prose-blockquote:before:left-0 md:prose-blockquote:before:w-[6px] prose-ol:pl-[16px] prose-ol:mb-[20px] prose-ol:list-decimal md:prose-ol:pl-[26px] prose-li:marker:proportional-nums prose-ul:pl-[16px] prose-ul:mb-[20px] prose-ul:list-disc md:prose-ul:pl-[26px] prose-li:font-500 prose-li:text-charcoal prose-li:text-[16px] prose-li:leading-[32px] prose-li:m-0 prose-li:p-0 prose-table:table-fixed prose-table:border-[0px] prose-table:text-charcoal prose-table:text-[14px] prose-table:leading-[24px] md:prose-table:text-[16px] prose-tr:grid prose-tr:divide-y-[3px] prose-tr:divide-lavender prose-tr:border-[0px] sm:prose-tr:border-[3px] sm:prose-tr:border-lavender sm:prose-tr:table-row prose-td:p-[32px] sm:prose-td:border-[3px] sm:prose-td:border-lavender prose-th:p-[32px] empty:prose-th:hidden sm:empty:prose-th:table-cell sm:prose-th:border-[3px] sm:prose-th:border-lavender prose-thead:border-[3px] prose-thead:border-lavender prose-tbody:border-[3px] prose-tbody:border-lavender prose-tbody:divide-y-[3px] prose-tbody:divide-lavender"><h2 id="whatarethetypicalresponsibilities">What Are The Typical Responsibilities?</h2>
<p>Retail&#xA0;sales&#xA0;associates&#xA0;are typically responsible for the following&#xA0;job duties:</p>
<ul>
<li>Greeting&#xA0;customers</li>
<li>Determining and fulfilling the&#xA0;customers' needs</li>
<li>Answering&#xA0;customers'&#xA0;questions&#xA0;about the store merchandise and&#xA0;store policies</li>
<li>Explaining and demonstrating a product's features and usages</li>
<li>Providing information about sales, discounts, loyalty programs, store&#xA0;credit cards, promotions, financing options, and other benefits</li>
<li>Encouraging customers to purchase products and suggesting the purchase of additional products</li>
<li>Arranging sales merchandise and keeping the&#xA0;sales floor&#xA0;tidy (such as folding clothing and returning misplaced items to the appropriate shelf)</li>
<li>Providing&#xA0;outstanding customer service&#xA0;by assisting customers throughout their shopping experience</li>
<li>Ringing up customer purchases on the&#xA0;cash register</li>
<li>Accepting orders,&#xA0;processing&#xA0;payments, and handling&#xA0;refunds</li>
<li>Counting money and making change</li>
<li>Bagging, boxing, or gift wrapping purchases</li>
<li>Stocking shelves&#xA0;and taking stock inventory</li>
</ul>
